The Sardinia Radio Telescope is a large, fully steerable radio telescope currently being completed near San Basilio, province of Cagliari in Sardinia, Italy. It is a collaboration among the Istituto di Radioastronomia di Bologna, the Cagliari Astronomy Observatory (Cagliari) and the Arcetri Astrophysical Observatory (Florence). It has been completed in 2011. The main technical points are: Coordinates: 392935N 91443E / 39.49306N 9.24528E / 39.49306; 9.24528
